<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 865.111/15</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Jay</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>548. Your telegrams 633 and 634, May 4 and 6. Inform Italian Government
                            no countries except Italy attempt to hold wives and children of
                            naturalized American citizens in order to induce latter to return for
                            military service. Say that this Government earnestly desires that wives
                            and children of naturalized American citizens now detained in Italy be
                            permitted to return this country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>